issue.body: closes #1759 closes https://github.com/w3c/aria/issues/2346 also closes https://github.com/w3c/core-aam/issues/149 This PR adjusts the requirements for `aria-setsize` to fix the inconsistency between the ARIA and CORE AAM specs regarding the use of `-1` as a value. # Test, Documentation and Implementation tracking Once this PR has been reviewed and has consensus from the working group, tests should be written and issues should be opened on browsers. issue.title: The edge menu should be closed when selection menu is open
issue.body:
![obrazek](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/75206927-8162-4928-bf44-95340c62194d)

On a side note: When only edges are selected and no class is selected, then the menu should be different and opened on the lastly selected edge.

comment.body:
The part about edge menu closing was implemented

> On a side note: When only edges are selected and no class is selected, then the menu should be different and opened on the lastly selected edge.

Unfortunately didn't have time to implement this. And since the rendering of edge toolbars is different than for nodes, the implementation wasn't as straightforward, so I didn't want to implement something half-baked, just for @skodapetr to have it rewrite couple of months later
